snippet.textDisplay: I can't help but feel bad for Conker. He only got 2 games! Donkey Kong got a few and even Banjo-Kazooie got 5! Conker only had 2. Conker's Pocket Tales, and Conker's Bad Fur Day. Live & Reloaded doesn't count because it's a ramake, Project Spark is a game that got Conker slapped on it so it would sell better (Conker's not even in the main game!) and Young Conker is an augmented reality game (doesn't count. I'm only counting MAIN games). Hell if you think about it.... Donkey Kong came back with Returns and Tropical Freeze. Banjo came back with the spiritual successor with Yooka-Laylee. What does Conker get? Stuck in Microsoft hell with no bright light in his immediate future. No spiritual successor, no comeback/sequel, nothing he's just dead, probably for good. I mean I know he doesn't have the following that say Banjo or Mario had/have but damn it he's still a great character and had an awesome game. He never got his chance to shine, he never got the chance to make something of himself, he has the two games and that's it. He didn't get half the screen time or credit he deserved. Hell there would've been a Conker's Other Bad Fur Day if Microsoft didn't cancel it. They had a story and everything! And instead he's just.......... gone. Really makes you sympathize with the poor critter.

snippet.textDisplay:
There were plenty of games before this one to be rated M, but this one is definitely significant for other reasons. I think it was the first game in this genre to be rated M. 3D platformers at that time were typically family friendly, and even today they don't usually go past a T rating (if even that).

I also think the content behind the M rating might be responsible for its controversy. Nintendo was fine with having other M-rated games on the N64 (Perfect Dark, Turok, etc.), but those earned their rating from violence. Conker was a lot more raunchy, with things like the sunflower and Buga the Knut.
